$ PowerShell cmdLet: convertTo-secureString

The → Windows/PowerShell/language/cmdlet `convertTo-secureString` converts plain text or encrypted strings to a «secure string» (which is → development/Data that is to be removed from memeory as soon as it is no longer needed).

{ -asPlainText -force

  When using the parameter `-asPlainText`, the cmdLet also requires that the paramter `-force` is specified.
  -
  The documentation says about `-force`:
  "
    Confirms that you understand the implications of using the AsPlainText parameter and still want to use it.
  "

}

sa:

  → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/secureString
